attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a highly capable DDoS bot, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt/Bashlite families targeting IoT devices. The sample contains implementation for numerous attack vectors including TCP SYN/ACK/XMAS/STOMP floods, UDP custom/plain/hex floods, SSDP (M-SEARCH) reflection, and Layer 7 HTTP/TLS floods using randomized User-Agent and Accept headers. It features process-killing logic (killer_init) to eliminate competing malware and targeted vulnerability scanners (gpon80, realtek). The bot connects to a hardcoded C2 server at 144.172.110.33 and uses a watchdog mechanism to maintain persistence.
